    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - SPEEDOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SPEEDOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to Speedometer in the OPERATION chapter of this manual for description of speedometer
                circuits.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x08245103">
            <title>Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</title>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Disconnect engine harness connector from the sensor. Loosen the lock nut and remove the
                        sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                        shavings or debris from the sensor.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the transmission speedometer gear,
                        then back out
                        <emph type="bold">one full turn</emph>. Tighten lock nut to 15 ft-lbs. (20.3 N&#8226;m). This
                        assures that the sensor is adjusted properly for the next test.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>To perform this test, construct two test leads using terminals (P/N 1680205C1) and suitable length of
                16 gauge wire. Install terminals on one end and alligator clips on the other.
            </para>
